  <!-- EN: Xuantian Sect—Part one -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookA.label>《玄天宗史记》其一</RI_Book_SectBookA.label>
  <!-- EN: The mountain mist swirled like a dragon, inhaling and exhaling the essence of the world. At the cliff’s edge stood Xu Tianming, once the son of a humble woodcutter. As a child, he found a fragment of an ancient text, though he knew nothing of spiritual energy. Blessed with innate talent, he studied the text and soon felt his mind flooded with memories, revealing a path to the Dao.\n\nAfter thirty years of hard work, he reached the Yuanying realm. He had battled demons and faced countless life-or-death trials.Focusing his mind, Xu Tianming’s body crackled with energy, and he attempted to withstand the heavenly lightning with his flesh. The lightning tore through him, breaking ancient bonds. He closed his eyes, feeling spiritual energy surge through him like a river. In that moment, he glimpsed the truth, and the lightning exploded into nothing.\n\nHe climbed to the peak, took his sword, and carved three words into the stone—"Xuantian Sect." -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookA.description>山雾缭绕，如苍龙盘桓，吞吐天地灵机，崖畔立着一名修士。许天明，原本不过是一介樵夫之子，出身微末，年幼时，他偶然拾得一卷残破的古籍□□□□斑驳。彼时，他尚不知灵气为何物，但他天生灵芽，资质过人，略加研读，便觉脑中多出无数记忆，自此，一条大道展现在他眼前。\n\n三十载寒暑，他隐于□□□□终至元婴境。无数次历险于邪妖之地，曾□□□□昼夜，几度生死一线。\n\n心思收回，周身刹那间电光四溢，许天明周身□□□□，竟妄图以肉身硬抗天雷。雷电贯穿血肉，筋骨作响□□□□某种枷锁正缓缓碎裂。他闭目感知，只觉天地灵气汹涌而来，如江河奔腾，流转全身。某一瞬，他似乎窥见了□□□□，雷光竟在其身旁炸裂，化作无形。\n\n他走至山巅，以剑为笔，在石壁上刻下三个大字——“玄天宗”。</RI_Book_SectBookA.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Story of An -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookB.label>《戊午年安氏小传》</RI_Book_SectBookB.label>
  <!-- EN: My name is An, a humble servant at Xuantian Sect, tasked with mundane duties like fetching water, chopping wood, and sweeping the grounds. Never did I dare to dream of cultivating the Dao, for my only wish was to live in peace, ensuring my daily survival. The sect, having stood for several decades, occupies seven islands in the East Sea and boasts great renown. Yet, the spiritual veins are scarce, making cultivation arduous for many of the disciples. As for us common servants, even the faintest trace of spiritual energy is beyond our reach. We endure only through hard work and perseverance.\n\nOne day, the Sect Master, Xu Zhenren, emerged from his retreat, leading the elders and disciples to the Northern Sea. There, they battled eight evil serpents for three days and nights, ultimately seizing the spiritual vein hidden beneath the sea. When the news returned, the entire sect was stirred, and even servants like me dared to hope for change.\n\nIn the following months, rumors of this victory spread both within and outside the sect. Yet, from a disciple I knew, I learned that the returning master and his disciples had closed themselves off in seclusion. He tried to eavesdrop on them, but the wards had been set up, and he returned empty-handed. I am at peace with myself, but each night, as I gaze at the sky, I feel an ominous chill in the air, and even the candles flicker uneasily. -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookB.description>吾名安氏，玄天宗一介杂役，平日烧火挑水，砍柴扫地，未敢奢望修道之机，只求温饱安生。宗门立派数十年，占东海七岛，声势煊赫，然灵脉稀薄，诸多师兄弟修行维艰，我等更是连些许灵气都沾不上，唯有苦力度日。\n\n某日，掌门许真人出关，亲率诸长老弟子远赴北海，与那八头邪蛇血战三日三夜，终夺得海底灵脉。消息传回，宗门上下尽皆振奋，连我等杂役下人亦心生盼望。\n\n此后数月，宗门内外皆传此事，但吾从一名相识的弟子口中得知，归来的掌门和弟子只是闭门不出。他曾前去偷听，谁知下了禁制，无功而返。吾问心无愧，只是每夜仰望苍穹，常觉阴风阵阵，连烛火都燃得不安稳。</RI_Book_SectBookB.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Master's Secret Letter #1 -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookC.label>掌门秘函#1</RI_Book_SectBookC.label>
  <!-- EN: To: Master Chai Yu,\n\nI am Xu Tianming, the Sect Master of Xuantian Sect. I recently returned to the sect and wish to report what I have seen and heard. Several years ago, I led the disciples of our sect aboard a starship, crossing the vast expanse of the void, in search of the spiritual source known as Lingbing. Over the course of several years, we encountered countless barren planets, their spiritual energy scarce. Despite consuming a large amount of spiritual stones, we found nothing.\n\nOn our return journey, the starship made a stop at an ancient planet, its surface covered in endless yellow sand, with only a few scattered villages. Here, one of my disciples encountered a young cultivator, garbed in blue, with a strikingly handsome appearance. With a smile, he said, "Lingbing has appeared, and the Great Yu shall rise. You children would be wise not to inquire further."\n\nAt his words, the disciples grew angry, and we left swiftly. However, doubts clouded my mind. Several years ago, I had already touched the threshold of the Earth Immortal realm, yet I felt that this man’s cultivation was far beyond my understanding. Thus, I write this letter to inform all of you, esteemed Sect Masters. Take a moment to reflect, and the rest I shall discuss when we meet.\n\nRespectfully,\nXu Tianming\n21st day of the Cold Moon, Bingyin Year -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookC.description>柴玉真人：\n\n吾名许天明，乃玄天宗掌门。近日归宗，谨将所见所闻呈上。几年前，吾带领宗门弟子，乘星舟横渡太虚，欲寻那唤作灵炳的灵气尽头。数年间，见识无数行星荒芜，灵气稀薄，虽消耗大量灵石，始终未能有所收获。\n\n回程途中，星舟停于一颗古老星球，黄沙漫漫，村落稀少。于此，弟子遇一青衣修士，容颜俊美，他微笑道：“灵炳现，大虞临，汝等小儿，少打听为妙。”\n\n此言一出，众人愠怒，于是匆匆离去。然我心中疑云密布，数年前我已触摸地仙门槛，却觉此人修为深不可测。是以，写此信以告知各位掌门，诸位可作一叹，余下之事，待面谈。\n\n许天明敬上\n丙寅年寒月21日</RI_Book_SectBookC.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Xuantian Sect—Part eight -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookD.label>《玄天宗史记》其八</RI_Book_SectBookD.label>
  <!-- EN: On this day, Sect Master Xu Tianming summoned the heroes to the main hall. The flickering candlelight cast long shadows, revealing the solemn expressions on the faces of all present. Xu Tianming held a secret letter, sealed with the stamps of the seven sect masters. The handwriting was hurried, almost illegible, as if written in haste. The letter read: "The strength of the Great Yu is not something a single sect can oppose."\n\nXu Tianming looked up, his gaze sweeping over the hundred death warriors gathered in the hall. These cultivators had been specially selected from various sects, each at the peak of the Nascent Soul stage, with three Earth Immortals leading them. Dressed in dark armor and carrying the sect's treasured artifacts, their eyes burned with determination. All knew the dangers that lay ahead.\n\nBefore they departed, Xu Tianming personally tied a Qinghun talisman around each warrior’s wrist. The talisman could summon a bird to carry messages across the stars. In a deep voice, he said, "This journey is perilous. May your martial fortunes be prosperous."\n\nThree months passed, and no bird returned. I write this now with a heavy heart, uncertain of the sect’s future. May future disciples read this record and understand the might of the Great Yu, proceeding with caution and care. -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookD.description>是日，宗主许天明召集群雄于大殿。殿中烛火摇曳，映得众人面色凝重。天明手持一卷密信，信上盖有七大派掌门印，字迹潦草，似仓促而成。信曰：“大虞之强，非一宗可敌。”\n\n许天明抬眼，望向殿中百名死士。这些修士皆是从各宗精选而出，修为最低也是元婴巅峰，更有三名地仙带领。他们身着玄甲，背负宗门至宝，目光如炬，此行凶险，众人皆知。临行前，掌门亲手为每人系上青魂符，符鸟振翅可传讯星河。他沉声道：“此行凶险，祝君武运昌隆。”\n\n第三月，再无符鸟归。余提笔记此，心中悲凉，不知宗门前路何在。愿后世弟子，观此记录，知大虞之强，慎之又慎。</RI_Book_SectBookD.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Master's Secret Letter #2 -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookE.label>掌门秘函#2</RI_Book_SectBookE.label>
  <!-- EN: To Sect Master Lin Miao of the Canglong Sect:\n\nThe truth of the Lingbing, we have pieced together. It is the source of all spiritual energy in the world, meant to flow endlessly and nourish all realms. Yet now, its energy has run dry, showing signs of exhaustion. Even more troubling, the Great Yu Empire has already seized vast amounts of this spiritual energy. Their national power is immense, and their cultivators’ realms far exceed our own — they are no longer a force we can contend with.\n\nAfter much thought, I fear that the future of the Xuantian Sect, and all other sects, may require a new strategy. If we cling to old methods, we will never overcome the might of the Great Yu. Therefore, I request that all sect masters convene at the Xuantian Sect to discuss countermeasures. Whether we join forces or find a new path, it must be decided together.\n\nI look forward to your swift arrival, to discuss the fate of our future.\n\nYours sincerely,\nXu Tianming\nJuly 3rd, Ji Chou Year -->
  <RI_Book_SectBookE.description>苍龙宗掌门林妙：\n\n灵炳之真相，吾等以拼凑完整，灵炳乃天地灵气之源，本应源源不绝，滋养万界。然今其灵气枯竭，似有衰竭之象。更令人忧者，大虞早已攫取海量灵气，其国力之强盛，修士境界之高，已非我等可敌。\n\n吾思之再三，玄天宗乃至诸派前路，恐需另谋良策。若固守旧法，终难敌大虞之威。故特请诸位掌门共聚玄天宗，商讨应对之策。或联袂共进，或另辟蹊径，皆需诸位共议。望诸位速至，共商大计。\n\n许天明敬上\n己丑年暑月3日</RI_Book_SectBookE.description>
  
